gnutls_dtls_get_timeout(3)                                                                        gnutls                                                                        gnutls_dtls_get_timeout(3)

NAME
       gnutls_dtls_get_timeout - API function

SYNOPSIS
       #include <gnutls/dtls.h>

       unsigned int gnutls_dtls_get_timeout(gnutls_session_t session);

ARGUMENTS
       gnutls_session_t session
                   is a gnutls_session_t type.

DESCRIPTION
       This  function  will  return  the milliseconds remaining for a retransmission of the previously sent handshake message. This function is useful when DTLS is used in non-blocking mode, to estimate
       when to call gnutls_handshake() if no packets have been received.

RETURNS
       the remaining time in milliseconds.

SINCE
       3.0

